licence_overview:
Under the [Wireless Telegraphy Act 1967,](http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/1967/72 "Wireless Telegraphy Act 1967"){:rel="external"} dealers who provide TV equipment (including video recorders and PC TV cards) for sale or hire must notify [TV Licensing](http://www.tvlicensing.co.uk/ "TV licensing"){:rel="external"} of customers' names and the address where the equipment is to be installed. 

You can now [register as a dealer online.](http://www.tvlicensing.co.uk/check-if-you-need-one/business-and-organisations/tv-dealers-AUD18 "Register as a dealer online"){:rel="external"}

%Failure to do so within 28 days of sale could result in prosecution and a financial penalty of up to £1,000.%
